10. How can you tell the difference between break and continue?
Break ->
      When we want to come out of loop use Break.
      This will break the current loop and we come out of loop.
Continue -> 
       When we want skip next line after continue statement at specific condition use Continue.
 
11. In a for loop, what is the difference between range(10), range(0, 10), and range(0, 10, 1)?
range(10) -> This will print 10 numbers 0 to 9.
range(0,10) -> Here we have give starting index from where we want to start 0 to end at 10 , This will also print 0 to 9 total 10 numbers.
range(0,10,1) -> Here we have give starting index, last index, and steps means how much steps to do , this will print 0 to 9 total 10 numbers.

12. Write a short program that prints the numbers 1 to 10 using a for loop. Then write an equivalent
program that prints the numbers 1 to 10 using a while loop.
for loop ->
          for i in range(1,11):
             print(i)
             
while loop ->
          num = 1
          while(num < 11):
             print(num)
             num += 1

13. If you had a function named bacon() inside a module named spam, how would you call it after
importing spam?
spam.bacon()
